1
00:00:01,210 --> 00:00:03,070
(Episode 65)

2
00:00:03,140 --> 00:00:04,180
Hello?

3
00:00:04,180 --> 00:00:07,410
So I finally get to meet Chae Hwa Young.

4
00:00:07,980 --> 00:00:09,110
I'll text you the address.

5
00:00:09,110 --> 00:00:11,620
Bring the 1,000,000 dollars
and come alone.

6
00:00:11,920 --> 00:00:15,420
Like I said, if you show up
with the cops or anyone else,

7
00:00:15,620 --> 00:00:20,390
- I will leak that video. Don't test me.
- Okay, I get it.

8
00:00:20,890 --> 00:00:21,960
I'll come alone.

9
00:00:22,660 --> 00:00:23,660
Don't worry.

10
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:35,370
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

11
00:00:36,110 --> 00:00:38,740
CEO Chae just got in a taxi
with a bag of money.

12
00:00:39,780 --> 00:00:42,150
Please, be safe, Baek Ho.

13
00:00:44,820 --> 00:00:47,420
This time, I will get my hands
on the definitive evidence...

14
00:00:48,220 --> 00:00:50,260
and expose the truth behind
Dad's wrongful death.

15
00:00:54,790 --> 00:00:57,730
Honey. What are you looking for?

16
00:00:58,160 --> 00:01:01,370
Do we have any old clothes?
Something I can wear once and toss.

17
00:01:01,530 --> 00:01:04,440
What are you talking about?
You don't have any old clothes, honey.

18
00:01:05,140 --> 00:01:07,840
But why do you need old clothes?
Where are you going?

19
00:01:08,210 --> 00:01:10,780
I'm going to check out a property.

20
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:15,650
If I look like I have money,
they won't give me a good price.

21
00:01:15,950 --> 00:01:18,520
A property?
You're going to look at real estate?

22
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:20,750
I'll find something for you. Let me.

23
00:01:21,050 --> 00:01:25,220
My goodness. It looks like he's finally
going to buy a building for our Hong Ju.

24
00:01:25,620 --> 00:01:29,590
That's more like it.
My husband is finally treating me right.

25
00:01:40,570 --> 00:01:41,570
Chae Hwa Young.

26
00:01:41,870 --> 00:01:45,310
She wouldn't have taken the USB with her
to meet the blackmailer.

27
00:01:45,780 --> 00:01:48,710
It wasn't at her house.
Which means it might be in here.

28
00:02:10,270 --> 00:02:11,800
The CEO has stepped out.

29
00:02:12,500 --> 00:02:13,940
Is she?

30
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:16,980
- General Manager Kang. There you are.
- Hello.

31
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:18,640
Hasn't Director Ma arrived yet?

32
00:02:27,190 --> 00:02:31,160
The CEO isn't even in.
What are you doing in here?

33
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:34,130
What does it look like I'm doing?
I'm taking a little break.

34
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:38,330
We should have a bed for staff wellness.
I mean, we work at a hotel.

35
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:39,900
But there's nowhere to lie down?
Does that make any sense?

36
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:41,370
You heard me, right, General Manager Kang?

37
00:02:41,630 --> 00:02:44,440
Should we put a massage chair or something
in the break room, then?

38
00:02:45,300 --> 00:02:48,610
General Manager Kang,
that's a ridiculous suggestion.

39
00:02:48,710 --> 00:02:51,480
Sitting all day is bad for your back,

40
00:02:51,910 --> 00:02:53,780
so let's look into it
as an employee benefit.

41
00:02:53,910 --> 00:02:57,550
Exactly. Now, can you please
not bother someone on their break...

42
00:02:57,720 --> 00:02:58,780
and just leave?

43
00:03:00,320 --> 00:03:02,990
What, are you just going to stay here
all day, Director Ma?

44
00:03:03,390 --> 00:03:04,420
Team Leader Jin.

45
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:08,260
You're not my supervisor,
so why are you policing my break time?

46
00:03:08,760 --> 00:03:10,560
Even General Manager Kang understands.

47
00:03:13,330 --> 00:03:15,770
Gosh, I was just trying
to take a ten-minute break.

48
00:03:16,070 --> 00:03:19,240
The way you're all acting,
people will think I just slack off.

49
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:23,780
By the way, General Manager Kang,
what brings you here?

50
00:03:25,610 --> 00:03:26,680
Team Leader Jin,

51
00:03:27,050 --> 00:03:30,420
- I'd like a word with Director Ma.
- All right then.

52
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:40,730
Director Ma.

53
00:03:41,690 --> 00:03:43,630
About what I said the other day...

54
00:03:43,630 --> 00:03:45,330
I feel bad about it.

55
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:47,870
So, I was wondering...

56
00:03:48,470 --> 00:03:49,630
if you'd like to have dinner tonight?

57
00:03:50,340 --> 00:03:51,340
Dinner?

58
00:03:51,670 --> 00:03:55,870
Yes. I'd like to apologize...

59
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:57,810
for how rude I've been to you.

60
00:03:58,210 --> 00:04:01,910
I can't today.
I have an important appointment.

61
00:04:02,210 --> 00:04:03,850
You do?

62
00:04:06,350 --> 00:04:08,320
This may be out of line,

63
00:04:09,220 --> 00:04:13,020
but what legal advice are you getting
from my brother, Baek Ho?

64
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:15,660
If there's anything I can do,
I'd be happy to help.

65
00:04:16,030 --> 00:04:18,960
It's a personal matter.

66
00:04:20,300 --> 00:04:23,100
I guess it's something
you can't tell me about?

67
00:04:23,840 --> 00:04:26,540
That's right. I should get going.

68
00:04:41,990 --> 00:04:43,960
Are you working from home today?

69
00:04:44,320 --> 00:04:47,990
Yes, I think so.
I can't focus at the library anyway.

70
00:04:48,730 --> 00:04:49,830
Okay, honey.

71
00:04:50,230 --> 00:04:52,600
In that case, I'll try to come home
a little early today.

72
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:54,600
Suit yourself.

73
00:04:55,670 --> 00:04:57,500
- See you later.
- Okay.

74
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:08,180
But still, who the heck is...

75
00:05:08,780 --> 00:05:12,780
blackmailing me and Hwa Young?
I wonder if she's found anything out.

76
00:05:13,520 --> 00:05:18,460
(Funny Funny Daycare Center)

77
00:05:21,760 --> 00:05:23,700
Unless this blackmailer
is a complete idiot,

78
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:27,600
there's no way he'd pick
a building with no escape route.

79
00:05:46,950 --> 00:05:48,450
Gosh, the third floor of a daycare...

80
00:05:49,050 --> 00:05:51,090
And of course there's no elevator.

81
00:05:51,860 --> 00:05:52,960
Gosh, I'm exhausted.

82
00:06:17,280 --> 00:06:18,750
You made it.

83
00:06:23,490 --> 00:06:24,520
Where are you?

84
00:06:26,060 --> 00:06:27,760
Stop hiding and come out!

85
00:06:33,230 --> 00:06:35,300
Well, well. Someone's impatient.

86
00:06:45,380 --> 00:06:46,410
The memory card?

87
00:06:47,010 --> 00:06:48,050
Hand it over first.

88
00:06:48,610 --> 00:06:52,650
- Don't try anything funny.
- Relax. Don't get so worked up.

89
00:06:53,520 --> 00:06:54,520
Is that the 1,000,000 dollars?

90
00:07:02,260 --> 00:07:04,600
Here. I had to carry this all the way
up to the third floor.

91
00:07:04,660 --> 00:07:06,230
Lugging this all the way
to the third floor.

92
00:07:09,100 --> 00:07:11,840
What do you think you're doing?
This wasn't the deal!

93
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:16,170
Do you really think
you can get away with this?

94
00:07:17,140 --> 00:07:19,740
How I get out of here is
none of your business.

95
00:07:22,450 --> 00:07:24,920
Give it to me.
I said, give me the memory card!

96
00:07:29,690 --> 00:07:31,060
Here, take it.

97
00:07:34,060 --> 00:07:36,060
Hey! What do you think you're doing?

98
00:07:36,430 --> 00:07:39,360
- Here you go.
- Are you kidding me? Let me go!

99
00:07:39,430 --> 00:07:40,500
Let me go!

100
00:07:46,540 --> 00:07:48,640
Hey! Give me the memory card!

101
00:07:50,340 --> 00:07:51,840
Here, take it.

102
00:08:00,590 --> 00:08:01,590
CEO Chae, are you all right?

103
00:08:02,020 --> 00:08:04,860
I'm heading up to the third floor now.
Just hang on.

104
00:08:08,460 --> 00:08:09,590
Is this the original?

105
00:08:10,630 --> 00:08:13,760
How am I supposed to know
if this is the original?

106
00:08:13,830 --> 00:08:15,070
Suit yourself.

107
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:17,870
I didn't even have to give it to you.
I was doing you a huge favor.

108
00:08:18,070 --> 00:08:20,370
You thief! Put that money down!

109
00:08:21,310 --> 00:08:22,310
CEO Chae!

110
00:08:23,210 --> 00:08:24,210
CEO Chae!

111
00:08:25,210 --> 00:08:26,210
CEO Chae!

112
00:08:26,880 --> 00:08:30,250
I knew it. I've been expecting your minion
to show up.

113
00:08:36,950 --> 00:08:39,460
No!

114
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:42,160
Manager Lee!
He's trying to jump out the window!

115
00:08:42,290 --> 00:08:44,660
Go, quick! Get him!

116
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:48,170
What the? Is he really going to jump?

117
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:51,570
The backyard!
Don't let him get away! Hurry!

118
00:08:51,670 --> 00:08:54,740
- Don't let him get away! Go!
- Right!

119
00:08:58,740 --> 00:09:01,050
(Funny Funny Daycare Center)

120
00:09:01,580 --> 00:09:02,580
What's going on?

121
00:09:07,350 --> 00:09:09,250
Driver, go ahead.

122
00:09:12,290 --> 00:09:14,730
Do I look like an idiot? Why would I jump?

123
00:09:27,770 --> 00:09:28,770
Lady.

124
00:09:29,510 --> 00:09:31,640
You really thought you could outsmart me?

125
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:36,310
I knew you'd bring your goons along.
As if I wouldn't have seen that coming.

126
00:09:56,370 --> 00:09:57,670
So you're the blackmailer.

127
00:10:01,370 --> 00:10:04,540
- Hey! Stop right there!
- And why would I do that?

128
00:10:15,650 --> 00:10:18,860
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

129
00:10:22,490 --> 00:10:24,300
Are you waiting for a call?

130
00:10:24,630 --> 00:10:27,930
- Why are you so interested in my life?
- Personal life?

131
00:10:28,670 --> 00:10:29,670
Director Ma.

132
00:10:30,570 --> 00:10:33,270
So you've found someone
you like besides Jun Ho?

133
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:34,770
Don't you have work to do,
Team Leader Jin?

134
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:36,340
Or will you stand there staring at me?

135
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:39,140
(Lawyer Kang Baek Ho)

136
00:10:46,380 --> 00:10:47,390
What was that?

137
00:10:48,190 --> 00:10:49,990
No way, could they be...

138
00:10:55,730 --> 00:10:56,730
Baek Ho?

139
00:10:57,230 --> 00:10:59,500
What happened? Are you all right?

140
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:02,870
What? You're near a mechanic's shop?

141
00:11:03,530 --> 00:11:05,240
By any chance, do you have the address?

142
00:11:05,470 --> 00:11:09,210
No, don't even think about coming here.
It's too dangerous for you.

143
00:11:09,340 --> 00:11:12,940
- Don't come here. I mean it. Got it?
- I'm hanging up.

144
00:11:15,210 --> 00:11:17,210
(Dream Hotel)

145
00:11:20,550 --> 00:11:23,190
Are you all right?
How's your head? Does it hurt?

146
00:11:23,690 --> 00:11:25,020
Yes, I'm fine.

147
00:11:26,060 --> 00:11:30,090
- Anyway, did you catch that truck driver?
- He wasn't working with the blackmailer.

148
00:11:30,430 --> 00:11:31,630
They weren't accomplices?

149
00:11:31,730 --> 00:11:34,830
Right. He said he was just paid
to have the truck on standby.

150
00:11:35,670 --> 00:11:38,940
Fortunately, the memory card from him
is the original.

151
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:42,310
The one from the dashcam
in Director Kim's car.

152
00:11:44,940 --> 00:11:47,280
It's a relief we at least got this,

153
00:11:48,180 --> 00:11:52,650
but I'm worried that bastard made a copy
of it somewhere.

154
00:11:53,220 --> 00:11:54,620
Catch him. Whatever it takes.

155
00:11:56,450 --> 00:11:59,020
What's the status on the tracker
we put in the bag?

156
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:00,560
Yes, that.

157
00:12:01,860 --> 00:12:03,730
I'm checking on it now.

158
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:05,800
(71 Hangwang Road)

159
00:12:06,760 --> 00:12:08,500
- It stopped.
- Go, now.

160
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:09,500
Yes, ma'am.

161
00:12:14,870 --> 00:12:16,040
Gosh, of all times.

162
00:12:20,140 --> 00:12:21,210
Yes, Professor.

163
00:12:21,610 --> 00:12:22,650
Hwa Young.

164
00:12:23,410 --> 00:12:24,820
Your voice...

165
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:29,590
It sounds a little off. Are you sick?

166
00:12:29,790 --> 00:12:31,290
What can I do for you, Professor?

167
00:12:31,590 --> 00:12:35,360
Somehow, I kept worrying about you,
so I decided to call.

168
00:12:35,790 --> 00:12:38,460
I'm not feeling well,
so I'm getting an IV.

169
00:12:38,530 --> 00:12:42,500
An IV drip? Why? What's wrong?
Are you hurt?

170
00:12:42,970 --> 00:12:46,370
- No wonder you sounded so weak.
- It's nothing serious.

171
00:12:46,870 --> 00:12:48,210
I'm just a little dizzy.

172
00:12:48,810 --> 00:12:50,570
It's nothing for you to worry about.

173
00:12:50,640 --> 00:12:53,410
How can I not worry?
Hearing that you're sick is...

174
00:12:53,680 --> 00:12:55,680
already breaking my heart.

175
00:12:55,750 --> 00:12:58,450
Nam Bong, there's no need for that.

176
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:02,350
I need to get some rest,
so I'm going to hang up now.

177
00:13:02,520 --> 00:13:05,460
All right, Hwa Young.
I hope you get well soon.

178
00:13:09,460 --> 00:13:13,430
I should've asked what hospital she's at.
If I went to comfort her,

179
00:13:14,170 --> 00:13:15,570
I'm sure it would've helped.

180
00:13:23,570 --> 00:13:24,780
Idiots.

181
00:13:32,220 --> 00:13:33,220
What's this?

182
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:35,750
Darn it.

183
00:13:37,620 --> 00:13:38,960
Son of a gun.

184
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:41,160
Those little punks thought
they could fool me?

185
00:13:42,160 --> 00:13:43,390
What's with the brick?

186
00:13:45,160 --> 00:13:46,960
All that trouble for nothing.

187
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:49,830
- Who are you?
- Me?

188
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:51,870
I'm the person you need.

189
00:13:52,770 --> 00:13:56,410
- Did you follow me? You got a death wish?
- Calm down. Just listen to me.

190
00:13:57,910 --> 00:13:59,310
I'm not with Chae Hwa Young.

191
00:14:00,010 --> 00:14:01,180
Give me the original.

192
00:14:01,650 --> 00:14:04,010
You've got to be kidding me.
And I'm supposed to believe you?

193
00:14:04,980 --> 00:14:05,980
Baek Ho!

194
00:14:07,450 --> 00:14:09,890
Jang Mi, why are you here?
I told you not to come.

195
00:14:10,050 --> 00:14:13,160
- Give that memory card to me.
- Darn it.

196
00:14:17,160 --> 00:14:20,700
You didn't actually give CEO Chae
the real dashcam footage, did you?

197
00:14:20,970 --> 00:14:23,070
Please, if you have a copy,
just give it to me. Please?

198
00:14:23,170 --> 00:14:26,240
- What did you do with the footage?
- Who the heck are you two?

199
00:14:26,540 --> 00:14:27,810
Who are you
to be looking for that footage?

200
00:14:27,870 --> 00:14:31,080
The man in the photo you sent was my dad.

201
00:14:31,710 --> 00:14:33,910
And he was wrongfully killed
by Chae Hwa Young.

202
00:14:34,780 --> 00:14:37,820
Please, I'm begging you,
give me that footage.

203
00:14:37,880 --> 00:14:40,950
What was on the footage?
At least tell us that.

204
00:14:42,150 --> 00:14:43,690
If you won't talk,
then you leave me no choice.

205
00:14:44,120 --> 00:14:45,690
We'll have to report you to the police.

206
00:14:45,690 --> 00:14:47,290
Then you'll be charged as a criminal...

207
00:14:47,790 --> 00:14:50,430
and you won't see a single cent.
Is that what you want?

208
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:56,070
How did you get your hands
on that dashcam footage?

209
00:14:57,100 --> 00:15:00,100
All right, then.
Promise you'll pay me first.

210
00:15:00,540 --> 00:15:02,440
Okay, I promise.

211
00:15:14,290 --> 00:15:17,660
Some young guy took his dad's car
while he was away on business...

212
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:19,660
and brought it in for repairs,
saying he'd gotten into a fender bender.

213
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:23,230
He told me his dad has multiple cars,
but he was begging and pleading with me,

214
00:15:23,290 --> 00:15:25,130
He was begging me to fix it fast.

215
00:15:25,660 --> 00:15:27,260
He was terrified of his dad finding out.

216
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:30,300
So he asked me to swap the memory card
with an identical one.

217
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:32,000
So I took a look before swapping it out.

218
00:15:36,510 --> 00:15:37,610
What the heck is this?

219
00:15:39,940 --> 00:15:41,050
A murder?

220
00:15:42,180 --> 00:15:45,150
After I finished the repairs,
I was watching the footage out of boredom.

221
00:15:45,680 --> 00:15:46,880
And I couldn't believe my eyes.

222
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:50,250
So, it must have been Director Kim's son
who brought the car in.

223
00:15:51,090 --> 00:15:52,820
Did Director Kim's son
see the footage too?

224
00:15:53,090 --> 00:15:54,430
No way he saw it.

225
00:15:54,890 --> 00:15:58,360
It looked like he crashed while drunk.
If he knew what was on it,

226
00:15:58,530 --> 00:16:00,500
do you think he would've just left
the dashcam's memory card behind?

227
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:04,870
So what you're saying is,
you gave her the original memory card?

228
00:16:05,970 --> 00:16:07,770
Hey, I need the money.

229
00:16:08,540 --> 00:16:10,010
It was no use to me.

230
00:16:10,610 --> 00:16:12,680
Are you even human?
You witnessed a murder,

231
00:16:12,740 --> 00:16:14,550
and your first thought was
to cash in on it?

232
00:16:14,610 --> 00:16:16,380
It's not like it was my dad who died.

233
00:16:16,650 --> 00:16:19,820
Then please, just testify for us.
I can pay you, too.

234
00:16:20,520 --> 00:16:22,690
Money? Are you serious?

235
00:16:25,020 --> 00:16:26,520
Crap. It's those guys.

236
00:16:27,160 --> 00:16:29,290
- Oh no.
- They're Chae Hwa Young's men.

237
00:16:30,060 --> 00:16:31,600
Jang Mi, this way!

238
00:16:41,340 --> 00:16:44,580
What in the world could be on
that dashcam footage?

239
00:16:44,810 --> 00:16:49,150
When your father was lying on the road,
he was already bleeding from a head wound.

240
00:16:49,710 --> 00:16:52,950
It's probably footage of Chae Hwa Young
and Manager Lee attacking your father.

241
00:16:54,590 --> 00:16:58,160
Dad was on the ground in the photo
the blackmailer sent, too.

242
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:05,500
Hey, Tae Pyung.

243
00:17:06,330 --> 00:17:07,560
Yes, we're fine.

244
00:17:08,770 --> 00:17:09,900
No, not yet.

245
00:17:11,670 --> 00:17:12,770
I'm about to tell her.

246
00:17:17,270 --> 00:17:20,140
Jang Mi.
There's somewhere I need to take you.

247
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:26,380
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

248
00:17:29,090 --> 00:17:30,220
It's going to be okay.

249
00:17:31,490 --> 00:17:33,590
- Okay.
- Don't be alarmed.

250
00:17:33,860 --> 00:17:35,630
- Why?
- Just a second.

251
00:17:40,230 --> 00:17:41,230
Jang...

252
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:44,600
It's Jang Mi.

253
00:17:45,070 --> 00:17:46,070
Mom.

254
00:17:46,970 --> 00:17:50,270
It's me, Mom. Your daughter, Jang Mi.

255
00:17:50,570 --> 00:17:53,140
Jang Mi's here. My dear Jang Mi.

256
00:17:54,010 --> 00:17:56,480
Jang Mi is pretty. My Jang Mi.

257
00:18:01,020 --> 00:18:02,050
Mom.

258
00:18:02,790 --> 00:18:07,460
Mom. I missed you so much, Mom.

259
00:18:10,060 --> 00:18:12,100
It's Jang Mi. My Jang Mi.

260
00:18:13,160 --> 00:18:14,300
Jang Mi is here.

261
00:18:15,170 --> 00:18:16,170
Jang Mi.

262
00:18:16,770 --> 00:18:18,100
Suk Hee's daughter.

263
00:18:19,070 --> 00:18:21,000
Mom.

264
00:18:33,250 --> 00:18:34,490
My dear Jang Mi.

265
00:18:36,520 --> 00:18:37,590
Yes, Mom.

266
00:18:38,320 --> 00:18:41,230
Baek Ho did something amazing
for me today.

267
00:18:43,290 --> 00:18:44,500
I like Baek Ho.

268
00:18:45,630 --> 00:18:49,770
I have the japchae you like.
Suk Hee made it.

269
00:18:50,930 --> 00:18:54,070
Then I'd love to have some.
It's been a while.

270
00:18:54,540 --> 00:18:57,510
- It looks delicious.
- Mom, give Baek Ho a big portion.

271
00:18:57,640 --> 00:18:58,840
There's plenty of japchae.

272
00:18:59,780 --> 00:19:01,450
Baek Ho has to eat.

273
00:19:09,390 --> 00:19:13,220
If we had just gotten that memory card,
we could've taken down Chae Hwa Young.

274
00:19:14,290 --> 00:19:15,490
I'm so frustrated.

275
00:19:16,160 --> 00:19:19,160
I'm sorry.
I should've ensured we got that card.

276
00:19:19,300 --> 00:19:21,300
I'm just so glad
you two weren't seriously hurt.

277
00:19:21,970 --> 00:19:26,340
- I'm sorry.
- Why sorry? I should be thanking you.

278
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:27,440
You have nothing to be sorry for.

279
00:19:28,470 --> 00:19:29,570
You've been through a lot.

280
00:19:30,210 --> 00:19:31,240
I'll go get the food ready.

281
00:19:31,540 --> 00:19:32,540
Okay.

282
00:19:35,710 --> 00:19:39,550
I'll make sure to find that blackmailer
and see if he has any copies.

283
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:43,520
No, don't.
I'm sure her people have him by now.

284
00:19:44,690 --> 00:19:46,160
It's infuriating and a huge letdown,

285
00:19:46,890 --> 00:19:50,030
but I'll just have to find another way
to make Chae Hwa Young pay for her crimes.

286
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:59,700
Director Kim,
why have you been so hard to reach?

287
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,770
Do you have any idea how many times
I've tried to reach you?

288
00:20:02,140 --> 00:20:05,110
CEO Chae, I've been on sick leave,

289
00:20:05,110 --> 00:20:06,740
so I couldn't take your call.

290
00:20:07,340 --> 00:20:11,850
It was a major operation.
So, what was it you needed?

291
00:20:13,020 --> 00:20:14,620
It's about your car in the lot.

292
00:20:15,290 --> 00:20:17,450
It looks like your son has been driving it
around lately,

293
00:20:17,850 --> 00:20:19,890
so I was wondering
if something was going on.

294
00:20:20,420 --> 00:20:22,660
I was just calling to confirm.

295
00:20:24,330 --> 00:20:25,360
I see.

296
00:20:26,930 --> 00:20:29,270
Make sure you recover well.

297
00:20:34,810 --> 00:20:37,540
- What's the update?
- We got him.

298
00:20:38,540 --> 00:20:43,280
So, was that blackmailer working alone,
or is someone pulling the strings?

299
00:20:43,450 --> 00:20:44,510
We're looking into it.

300
00:20:44,650 --> 00:20:48,550
Check if he copied it to another USB,

301
00:20:48,750 --> 00:20:50,190
and destroy every last one of them.

302
00:20:50,320 --> 00:20:52,890
My guys are interrogating him now,
so we'll handle it without a hitch.

303
00:20:53,620 --> 00:20:56,790
The nerve of him.
How dare he try to blackmail me?

304
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:06,740
I told you, I didn't make any copies!

305
00:21:08,210 --> 00:21:09,270
That was the only one, I swear.

306
00:21:10,140 --> 00:21:12,210
What? Please, you have to believe me.

307
00:21:13,340 --> 00:21:15,280
I'm not smart enough to think of that.

308
00:21:15,280 --> 00:21:16,680
Please...

309
00:21:17,850 --> 00:21:19,420
I swear I didn't make any copies.

310
00:21:28,060 --> 00:21:29,430
Chairman Ma,

311
00:21:30,430 --> 00:21:31,800
I have a favor to ask you.

312
00:21:33,300 --> 00:21:34,300
A favor?

313
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:37,330
(Lawyer Kang Baek Ho)

314
00:21:42,610 --> 00:21:44,040
Yes, Lawyer Kang Baek Ho speaking.

315
00:21:44,340 --> 00:21:46,940
This is Ma Dae Chang.

316
00:21:47,840 --> 00:21:50,650
- I'm sorry?
- Chairman Ma of Dream Group.

317
00:21:50,980 --> 00:21:53,020
Yes, hello, sir.

318
00:21:53,820 --> 00:21:57,690
- So, what is this regarding?
- Our Team Leader Jin...

319
00:21:57,990 --> 00:22:01,690
was telling me
you've been a great help to her.

320
00:22:02,060 --> 00:22:03,930
It was nothing major.

321
00:22:04,290 --> 00:22:08,000
But Team Leader Jin was treated unfairly
by CEO Chae,

322
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:09,530
so I offered her some simple legal advice.

323
00:22:09,830 --> 00:22:12,970
Workplace harassment is a sensitive issue
these days, you know.

324
00:22:13,170 --> 00:22:16,440
The reason CEO Chae treated
Team Leader Jin that way.

325
00:22:16,770 --> 00:22:19,310
That's what's important here,
don't you think?

326
00:22:20,610 --> 00:22:22,980
Alright, Team Leader Jin,
go on and explain.

327
00:22:23,680 --> 00:22:25,680
I mean...

328
00:22:26,080 --> 00:22:30,320
She wrongly blames me for everything
that's happened to her lately.

329
00:22:30,950 --> 00:22:33,660
She's framing me
without a shred of evidence.

330
00:22:33,990 --> 00:22:35,660
Did you hear that, Lawyer Kang?

331
00:22:35,990 --> 00:22:36,990
Yes, I did.

332
00:22:37,330 --> 00:22:41,160
In that case, even if she's her supervisor
and the CEO,

333
00:22:41,430 --> 00:22:43,230
the company needs to launch
an official investigation.

334
00:22:43,670 --> 00:22:45,500
After all, managing CEO risk is crucial.

335
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:48,000
Exactly. You're right about that.

336
00:22:48,740 --> 00:22:51,580
Every word the CEO says,
every single action...

337
00:22:52,080 --> 00:22:55,050
has a huge impact on our stock price.

338
00:22:55,580 --> 00:22:59,680
Listen, Lawyer Kang,
how would you feel about working for us?

339
00:23:09,160 --> 00:23:10,360
My dear Jun Ho.

340
00:23:11,660 --> 00:23:15,730
I'm his mother, yet I can't even make him
a proper home-cooked meal.

341
00:23:29,380 --> 00:23:31,650
Hello, CEO Chae.

342
00:23:33,550 --> 00:23:35,120
What do you mean, late?

343
00:23:35,450 --> 00:23:38,560
Not at all.
For us, the night is still young.

344
00:23:38,860 --> 00:23:40,690
I'm calling because
I wanted to ask you something.

345
00:23:41,890 --> 00:23:44,760
I'm thinking of inviting
General Manager Kang Jun Ho to my home,

346
00:23:45,130 --> 00:23:48,570
but I'm not sure what he likes to eat.

347
00:23:49,630 --> 00:23:51,000
I'd hate to invite him over...

348
00:23:51,430 --> 00:23:54,840
only to serve him food
that he doesn't like.

349
00:23:56,640 --> 00:23:58,480
Our Jun Ho...

350
00:23:58,710 --> 00:24:01,880
loves a good, hearty kimchi stew
with pork.

351
00:24:02,350 --> 00:24:05,820
You know, the kind with sour kimchi
and plenty of pork,

352
00:24:05,880 --> 00:24:10,450
- with tofu, all simmered together?
- Right.

353
00:24:10,690 --> 00:24:13,290
Jun Ho was in the US for a long time,

354
00:24:13,690 --> 00:24:16,360
so he got sick and tired of Western food.

355
00:24:16,860 --> 00:24:20,660
In fact, he said he preferred Korean food
even when he worked at a restaurant.

356
00:24:22,830 --> 00:24:25,740
Jun Ho always says
the kimchi stew I make is...

357
00:24:25,800 --> 00:24:27,900
the most delicious thing in the world.

358
00:24:30,210 --> 00:24:31,210
I see.

359
00:24:32,140 --> 00:24:34,010
Thank you so much for telling me.

360
00:24:34,710 --> 00:24:38,320
Please, don't thank me.
I'm the one who should be thanking you.

361
00:24:38,780 --> 00:24:43,450
For thinking so highly of our Jun Ho
and inviting him as a son-in-law,

362
00:24:43,790 --> 00:24:45,860
I can't tell you how grateful I am.

363
00:24:46,490 --> 00:24:48,260
All right, goodbye.

364
00:24:50,590 --> 00:24:52,260
She's inviting Jun Ho over?

365
00:24:57,030 --> 00:24:58,030
I'm home.

366
00:25:03,340 --> 00:25:06,340
And all this time, I didn't even know
that's the kind of food my Jun Ho likes.

367
00:25:08,810 --> 00:25:10,110
I'm so sorry, Jun Ho.

368
00:25:13,420 --> 00:25:14,750
Mom is so sorry.

369
00:25:20,720 --> 00:25:23,760
- The CEO asked you about that?
- She did.

370
00:25:24,360 --> 00:25:28,470
She sees you as a potential son-in-law,
so she wants to know all about you.

371
00:25:28,530 --> 00:25:29,630
Son-in-law? Don't be ridiculous.

372
00:25:30,300 --> 00:25:32,900
- Don't get your hopes up.
- Seriously?

373
00:25:33,070 --> 00:25:36,610
Do you hate the idea of Jun Ho marrying
into the rich family behind Dream Group?

374
00:25:37,340 --> 00:25:39,140
You should focus on succeeding
on your own merit.

375
00:25:39,510 --> 00:25:41,180
Don't rely on a lucky break like this.

376
00:25:41,380 --> 00:25:44,180
Since CEO Chae is making such an effort,

377
00:25:44,510 --> 00:25:48,250
we should bring a really nice gift,
don't you think?

378
00:25:48,990 --> 00:25:52,660
I'll pick out a gift for you
that's beyond reproach.

379
00:25:52,790 --> 00:25:56,490
- Honey, why go to all that trouble?
- Why are you getting so upset?

380
00:25:56,960 --> 00:25:58,730
It's only proper to show our respect.

381
00:25:59,700 --> 00:26:01,300
You're being really strange.

382
00:26:02,700 --> 00:26:04,730
Fine, whatever. Do what you want.

383
00:26:05,300 --> 00:26:06,570
So strange.

384
00:26:07,500 --> 00:26:09,710
- I'm back!
- What are you doing here again?

385
00:26:10,710 --> 00:26:12,080
Did you finish up that urgent thing
you had to do?

386
00:26:12,440 --> 00:26:15,810
Yes. I have a trial tomorrow,
so I wrapped it up and came straight here.

387
00:26:16,180 --> 00:26:19,180
- So I could see you a little longer.
- Hey! That's so cheesy.

388
00:26:19,250 --> 00:26:20,680
Then plug your ears, man.

389
00:26:21,520 --> 00:26:24,050
I should get going.
As much as I'd like to stay.

390
00:26:24,450 --> 00:26:25,990
Then let me take you home.

391
00:26:26,360 --> 00:26:28,390
That way I can spend
a little more time with you.

392
00:26:28,490 --> 00:26:31,460
Hey, give it a rest, will you?

393
00:26:32,060 --> 00:26:35,330
- Get out. Out! Get out of here, you jerk!
- Hey, I'm just getting started.

394
00:26:35,400 --> 00:26:38,440
I said get out, man! Hurry up and go!
You, out! Jang Mi, you get out too! Go!

395
00:26:48,710 --> 00:26:51,250
I hate to see you go,
but you should head in, Jang Mi.

396
00:26:54,820 --> 00:26:55,820
Baek Ho.

397
00:26:56,550 --> 00:26:57,720
Actually, tomorrow...

398
00:26:58,150 --> 00:26:59,160
What?

399
00:27:12,440 --> 00:27:13,440
What's that?

400
00:27:13,940 --> 00:27:15,870
Why is that unfamiliar car parked there?

401
00:27:18,640 --> 00:27:20,180
Could it be an accomplice?

402
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:33,360
Baek Ho, what do we do?

403
00:27:34,260 --> 00:27:35,260
Wait...

404
00:27:39,060 --> 00:27:41,230
Excuse me, why are you parked
in front of my house?

405
00:27:42,470 --> 00:27:43,500
Come out here right now!

406
00:28:24,610 --> 00:28:26,140
(The First Man)

407
00:28:26,210 --> 00:28:27,680
I'll get straight to the point.

408
00:28:27,980 --> 00:28:31,150
Did you approach Jang Mi
because she resembles Director Ma Seo Rin?

409
00:28:31,780 --> 00:28:33,080
Something's not right.

410
00:28:33,420 --> 00:28:35,190
She doesn't seem like my Seo Rin.

411
00:28:35,190 --> 00:28:37,120
A burglar! There's a burglar!

412
00:28:38,720 --> 00:28:42,130
While listening to my Seo Rin
play the violin for us after so long.

413
00:28:42,360 --> 00:28:44,890
- The violin?
- If she really is Oh Jang Mi,

414
00:28:45,160 --> 00:28:47,300
would she even know
how to play the violin?

415
00:28:48,870 --> 00:28:50,870
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
